Frequently Asked Questions

Find answers to common questions about our professional foot care services

{/* FAQ Section */}
FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

Common Questions About Our Foot Care Services

Find answers to the most common questions about our mobile foot care services, booking process, and safety protocols.

Service Area & Location

Where do you provide services?

We provide mobile foot care services throughout Calgary and surrounding areas, including Airdrie, Cochrane, Okotoks, and Chestermere. We come directly to your home, care facility, or retirement home.

Do you have a clinic location?

We specialize in mobile services, bringing professional foot care directly to you. This ensures comfort and convenience, especially for seniors and those with mobility challenges.

How far do you travel?

We typically serve within a 50km radius of Calgary. For locations outside this area, please contact us to discuss availability and potential travel fees.

Payment & Insurance

What payment methods do you accept?

We accept electronic transfer (eTransfer), cash, cheque, and offer insurance direct billing for eligible plans. Payment is due at the time of service.

Do you direct bill insurance?

Yes, we offer direct billing for many insurance plans. Please contact us with your insurance information to verify coverage and eligibility.

What are your service rates?

Our comprehensive 30-40 minute assessments are competitively priced. Contact us for current rates and package options for regular maintenance care.

Equipment & Safety

How do you ensure sterile conditions?

We use only sterile, single-use instruments for each client. All equipment is professionally sterilized, and we follow strict infection prevention protocols to ensure your safety.

What equipment do you bring?

We bring all necessary professional equipment including podiatry drill, sterile instruments, ONYFIX application tools, and specialized wound care supplies. You don't need to provide anything.

Are your services safe for diabetics?

Absolutely. We specialize in diabetic foot care with advanced training in wound prevention and management. Our sterile protocols are especially important for diabetic patients.

Booking & Appointments

How do I book an appointment?

You can book by calling (403) 903-4293, using our online booking form, or sending an email. We typically respond within 24 hours to schedule your appointment.

How long is each appointment?

Our comprehensive assessments take 30-40 minutes, allowing time for thorough examination, treatment, and patient education. This ensures quality care without rushing.

Do you offer regular maintenance schedules?

Yes, we recommend regular maintenance every 6-8 weeks for optimal foot health. We can set up recurring appointments to ensure consistent care and early problem detection.

What if I need to cancel or reschedule?

Please provide 24-hour notice for cancellations or rescheduling. We understand that health situations can change and will work with you to find suitable alternative times.

Still Have Questions?

We're here to help! Contact us directly for any additional questions about our services, scheduling, or specific foot care needs.
